[Nouns] silence; stillness (quiet) [more]; peace, hush, lull; muteness [more]; solemn silence, awful silence, dead silence, deathlike silence.
[Verbs] be silent; hold one's tongue (not speak) [more].
render silent; silence, still, hush; stifle, muffle, stop; muzzle, put to silence (render mute) [more].
[Adjectives] silent; still, stilly; noiseless, soundless; hushed; mute [more].
soft, solemn, awful, deathlike, silent as the grave; inaudible (faint) [more].
[Adverbs] silently; sub silentio.
